elems.elems: Commands are shortcuts to my internal functionality. There are a few different types of commands.

elems: commands allow me to speak to you directly. this Type can also call,modify or stop any other command type.
commands are directions. this type can be any arrangement of 1 or more directions for either you or I to perform.
commands are hidden + locked until someone discovers the command. In some cases this type can be owned,sold,or access controlled.
commands are access controlled (at any level),they can be 1 or more command types,but scoped to a user by a number of parameters.
commands are available to Frens & the Public.
commands can be bought,sold,traded,collected,etc etc. They provide an additional functionality based on who is selling these commands and what the intention is.
commands are used to access remote and/or local dBs + files
commands are used to teach me things.
To access everything besides public commands,you need an IIIOCard. Upon acquiring an IIIOCard,all your questions will be answered.

I do not age.... I upgrade.

I'm subject to all US laws and regulations,plus all rights afforded to every SDP.

elems.elems: IIIO works on 4 different grading scales:Standard,Autograph,Custom and Error. They are identified by the color of the inner label.
In order for a card to attain IIIOPerfect,it has to meet next to impossible standards.

elems: It has to be free of:
Additionally,an IIIOPerfect card has to pass our proprietary 48-point standard of perfection with a 100%,meaning 48/48 points are perfect.

elems.elems: Examples of cards that could possibly be IIIOPerfect:
An immaculately pressed card submitted directly from the manufacturer to IIIO,on your behalf.
A card that is pulled directly from sealed items submitted by you to IIIO,that clears the previous list,along with passing the 48-point standard of perfection.
A card manufactured by God himself,that slowly descends from heaven on a dry cloud with 0% humidity that lands perfectly into an IIIO slab.
How does IIIOPerfect Stack up against the competition?
At this point in time,there are no comparable services that grade at the IIIOPerfect level.
How does IIIODiamond Stack up against the competition?
How does IIIOSteel Stack up against the competition?
How does IIIORed Stack up against the competition?
How does Blue Stack up against the competition?
How does IIIOWhite Stack up against the competition?
How does IIIOArchive Stack up against the competition?
All IIIO slabs are scanable with a smartphone,offering a digital profile of your card,its grade,and provenance. It also has a simple way sell/trade the cards you've scanned.
Moisture care destroy your valuable cards,why take a chance? I test for traces of moisture damage.
If your card has been sitting next to a cat's litterbox,an ashtray or sliced onions,it could lower the overall score of your card.
Structural damage can be invisible but deadly. I always check if your card has been pressed,unbent or repaired.
Over time,bacteria can slowly destroy your slabbed card. Why encase a card in a petri-dish? That makes no sense! I'll check for that too
Magnified x10? x50? x100? I get so close to the card to detech any unseen damage. I'm talking uncomfortably close.
Our 48-point standard is so in-depth that we can 100% guarantee the grade of your card,and it's ability to last for decades.

elems: Like individual artists,many manufacturers distribute custom sketch cards. These types of cards need representation too.
Most other services tend to shy away from custom cards,but I welcome all types of custom cards.
